## Coverage thresholds (risk-tiered, mutation-aware)

Coverage % is a vanity metric on its own. Mutation score is the honest fitness function. Tier modules by business risk:

| Tier | Examples | Line cov | Branch cov | Mutation score |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **High-risk** | payment, auth, RLS, billing, AI-tool dispatch | 80% | 70% | 75% |
| **Mid-risk** | orchestrators, business logic, schema migrations | 70% | 60% | 60% |
| **Low-risk** | UI presentation, glue, formatters | 50% | — | — (advisory) |
| **Excluded** | generated, vendored, configs, scaffolds | — | — | — |

Stryker `break: <high-risk-mutation>` in CI = hard gate. Don't break the build on low-risk advisory tier.

